5. Why do we use Matplotlib for pie charts?

Matplotlib handles pie charts better (Seaborn doesn't support them):

python
# Matplotlib pie (works perfectly)
dept_counts = df['department'].value_counts()
plt.pie(dept_counts.values, labels=dept_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')

Seaborn limitation: Focuses on statistical/relational plots, not proportions.
